tic treatments, and the insights of the disability rights movement, Nick O’Brien examines how the everyday regulation of street-level bureaucracy can play an integral part in reimagining postliberal politics and the role of the law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJustice, Administration ofxPolitical aspects. 0aLawxPolitical aspects. 0aLawxSocial aspects. 7aLAW / Administrative Law & Regulatory Practice.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311119679440uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781529230611?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529230611423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529230611/original  a978-3-11-119679-4  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles